Package stonehorse.grit

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Associative<K,V>
    Associative composition of homogeneous values where modification is expression.
    Indexed<T>
    Sequentially indexed composition of homogeneous values where modification is expression.
    Lookup<V>
    Composite where homogeneous values can be looked up by key
    PersistentMap<K,V>
    A read only map where mutation is expression.
    PersistentSet<T>
    A read only set structure where mutation is expression.
    PersistentStack<T>
    A stack of elements where mutation is expression
    PersistentVector<T>
    A random access sequential collection with mutation as expression.
    Randomly<T>
    Composite where homogeneous members are randomly accessible by integer index
    Traversable<T>
    The most basic strict higher order application on sequential types
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Maps
    Creation of persistent Associative Map structures that accept null as ordinary valid key value.
    SerializedMap<K,V>
    Placeholder for serial maps, implemented as a simple sequence of key value pairs
    SerializedSet<V>
    Placeholder for serial sets, implemented as a simple sequence of values
    SerializedVector
    Placeholder for serial vectors, implemented as a simple sequence of values
    Sets
    Creation of persistent Set structures that accept null as ordinary valid value.
    Vectors
    Creation of persistent sequential vector structures.
